  "title": "Lumbar plexus",
  "body_html": "<div>The lumbar plexus is formed from the anterior rami of L1 to L4 with contributions from the subcostal nerve (T12).<br /><br /><div class=\"table-responsive\"><table class = \"tlarge table table-striped table-bordered\"  data-role=\"table\" id=\"tableid1\" ><thead><tr><th>Nerve</th><th>Origin</th><th>Structures supplied (motor)</th><th>Cutaneous supply</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Iliohypogastric</td><td>T12-L1</td><td>Internal oblique<br />Transversus abdominis</td><td>Anterior cutaneous ramus<br />Lateral cutaneous ramus</td></tr><tr><td>Ilioinguinal</td><td>L1</td><td>Internal oblique<br />Transversus abdominis</td><td>Anterior scrotal nerves in males<br />Anterior labial nerves in females</td></tr><tr><td>Genitofemoral</td><td>L1-L2</td><td>Cremaster</td><td>Femoral ramus<br />Genital ramus</td></tr><tr><td>Lateral femoral cutaneous</td><td>L2-L3</td><td>No motor function</td><td>Lateral femoral cutaneous</td></tr><tr><td>Obturator</td><td>L2-L4</td><td>Obturator externus<br />Adductor longus<br />Adductor brevis<br />Gracilis<br />Pectineus<br />Adductor magnus</td><td>Cutaneous ramus</td></tr><tr><td>Femoral</td><td>L2-L4</td><td>Iliopsoas<br />Pectineus<br />Sartorius<br />Quadriceps femoris</td><td>Anterior cutaneous branches<br />Saphenous</td></tr><tr><td>Short Direct Branches</td><td>T12-L4</td><td>Psoas major<br />Quadratus lumborum</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table></div><br /><i>Diagrams illustrating the lumbar plexus</i><br /><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb144b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb144.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/lumbar plexus'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb144b.png'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></div><br /><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb145b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb145.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/lumbar plexus'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb145b.png'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></div><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb079b.png'><img class='ajaximage' src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb079.png'/></a></td></tr><tr><td valign='top' align='left'> <span style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;'>Image sourced from </span><a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/lumbar plexus'  target='_blank' style = 'font-size:11px; color:LightGray;' >Wikipedia</a></td><td align='right'><a data-fancybox class='fancybox lbmagglasslink' rel='group' href='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/images_MRCEMnotes/swb079b.png'><img src='https://d20g8jnrcgqmxh.cloudfront.net/css/images/mag_glass.png'/></a></td></tr></table></div><br /><div class=\"text-center\"><table><tr><td align = 'left' colspan='2'><a data-fancyb